<p style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;"><span style=" font-weight:600;">When enough is not enough, saving will actually become irresponsible, harmful, and even evil.</span></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;"><li style=" font-weight:600;" style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;"><span style=" font-weight:400;">Constantly focusing on hoarding goods and savings and wealth to the point where it's actually distracting you from being able to be content, there will never be enough to be content.</span></li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Risking what you have to get even more will usually result in losing it and then what do you have to show for everything you had?</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Investing for your children to never have to work usually ends up in spoiled children that squander the wealth they've been given.</li></ul></body></html>